excerpt: Microbrewery for ales & IPAs, plus an American restaurant, bar, patio dining & a gift shop.
detail_description: Moab Brewery is a renowned microbrewery in Moab, offering a diverse selection of handcrafted beers and hearty American cuisine with a Southwestern twist. The brewery features an energetic atmosphere and also includes an American restaurant, bar, patio dining area, and a gift shop. Additionally, Moab is known as a haven for off-road enthusiasts with numerous bike shops available for renting top-quality bikes.
name: Moab Brewery
address: 686 S Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Moab is a city in eastern Utah. Itâ€™s a gateway to massive red rock formations in Arches National Park. Southwest, Canyonlands National Park features mesas and buttes carved by the Green and Colorado rivers, plus Native American rock art. Dinosaur tracks can be found at sites like Bull Canyon Overlook and Copper Ridge. In the city, collections at the Museum of Moab include dinosaur bones and archaeological artifacts.
detail_description: Moab, located in eastern Utah, serves as a gateway to the stunning red rock formations of Arches National Park and the mesas and buttes of Canyonlands National Park. The area also boasts Native American rock art and dinosaur tracks at sites like Bull Canyon Overlook and Copper Ridge. In addition to its natural wonders, Moab is home to the Museum of Moab, which showcases dinosaur bones and archaeological artifacts.
name: Moab
address: Utah 84532, USA

detail_description: Arches National Park, located in Moab, Utah, is a stunning destination with the Colorado River flowing nearby. Visitors can enjoy guided van tours and various rafting trips on the river, including whitewater adventures. The park offers well-worn paths for hiking and opportunities to explore petroglyphs and dinosaur tracks. Additionally, visitors can partake in activities such as road biking and scooter riding.
name: Arches National Park
address: Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Popular 9,000-acre recreation area including the noted Slickrock bike trail, jeep trails & camping.
detail_description: Sand Flats Recreation Area in Moab, Utah is a 9,000-acre nature recreation area nestled in a valley surrounded by striking red rock formations. It's a popular destination for campers, bikers, and off-road enthusiasts. The area offers thrilling activities such as mountain biking along the petrified dunes of the Slickrock Trail and Porcupine Rim Trail, as well as driving on the challenging Hells Revenge trail.
name: Sand Flats Recreation Area
address: Sand Flats Rd, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Challenging cycling area with a loop trail, picnic tables & toilets in a striking desert setting.
detail_description: Slickrock Bike Trail is a challenging cycling area located in a striking desert setting in Moab. The 12-mile loop trail offers a thrilling experience for beginners and experienced riders alike. With picnic tables, toilets, and plenty of water and sunscreen, it's an adventure worth the effort. Moab offers various outdoor activities such as river rafting on the Colorado River and exploring ancient petroglyphs along Potash Road.
name: Slickrock Bike Trail
address: Parking lot, Sand Flats Rd, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Down-to-earth food truck park featuring outlets with classic street fare, plus seating areas.
detail_description: Nestled in Moab, the Moab Food Truck Park is a casual and inviting spot that brings together a diverse range of food trucks offering classic street fare. Whether you're craving Chinese cuisine from Red Wok Chinese Express, authentic Mexican flavors from Tacos El Gordo, refreshing shave ice from Hokulia Shave Ice, or indulgent donuts from Delicate Donuts, this park has something to please every palate.
name: Moab Food Truck Park
address: 39 W 100 N, Moab, UT 84532, USA

detail_description: When planning a trip to Moab, it's recommended to allocate three full days for exploring the area. The Moab Rock Shop is a must-visit retail store and museum that offers an extensive collection of geological treasures such as crystals, dinosaur bones, fossils, gemstones, meteorites, mineral specimens, and petrified wood. Additionally, visitors can find antiques, books, maps, and various tools at the shop.
name: Moab Rock Shop
address: 600 N Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Cultural & natural history museum with geology, paleontology & archeology collections.
detail_description: The Moab Museum is a cultural and natural history museum that showcases collections related to geology, paleontology, and archaeology. It provides insights into the region's rich history, from Native American tribes to prospectors and Mormon pioneers. Visitors can learn about local geology, culture, and history while viewing life-size replicas of dinosaurs at the Moab Giants Dinosaur Park. The museum is conveniently located within walking distance from downtown Moab and offers a fascinating way to explore the area's heritage.
name: Moab Museum
address: 118 E Center St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Offroad driving route for 4x4 vehicles in a dramatic landscape of sandy bluffs & slickrock.
detail_description: Hells Revenge Safari Route is an exhilarating off-road driving experience designed for 4x4 vehicles, set against a stunning backdrop of sandy bluffs and slickrock. The route offers a range of exciting activities, from exploring Hells Revenge and Kens Lake to witnessing iconic spots like Thelma and Louise Point. The surrounding national parks, including Arches National Park with its natural arches and Canyonlands National Park with remote desert terrain, provide unparalleled natural beauty.
name: Hells Revenge Safari Rte
address: Utah 84532, USA

excerpt: Traditional steak & seafood spot with 4 dining rooms, 3 patios & panoramic mountaintop views.
detail_description: Nestled in Moab, Sunset Grill is a classic steak and seafood restaurant offering four dining rooms, three patios, and stunning mountaintop vistas. This spot is perfect for a romantic Valentine's Day dinner with its special menus and offers. The restaurant boasts a rich history as it was once the lavish mansion of Charlie Steen, the prominent figure of the Uranium Boom. Guests can enjoy not only delectable cuisine but also panoramic views of Moab from this historic establishment.
name: Sunset Grill
address: 900 N Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

detail_description: Moab Adventure Center is a central hub for outdoor activities in the stunning landscapes of southern Utah. It offers thrilling water excursions, including customizable jet boat tours that take guests behind Canyonlands National Park to admire the river scenery. Additionally, visitors can enjoy smooth floats and experience smaller rapids on guided tours starting from the Westwater Ranger Station. The center provides endless possibilities for exploration and adventure in Moab, promising an unforgettable experience for all who visit.
name: Moab Adventure Center
address: 225 S Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Upscale venue plating adventurous Southwestern cuisine in an intimate setting with a wine cellar.
detail_description: Desert Bistro is an upscale dining venue located in Moab, offering a unique blend of Southwestern and French cuisine in an intimate setting. The restaurant is known for its inventive menu featuring nightly game specials and fresh seafood flown in from the coast. With a focus on locally sourced ingredients, the bistro provides a sophisticated culinary experience that captures the spirit of Moab.
name: Desert Bistro
address: 36 S 100 W, Moab, UT 84532, USA

detail_description: Paddle Moab is a family-owned adventure company in Moab, Utah, offering stand-up paddleboarding (SUP), whitewater rafting, canyoneering, and other outdoor activities. They provide various paddleboarding trip options suitable for all levels of experience. The company's qualified instructors lead the tours and lessons, ensuring a safe and enjoyable experience for participants. Customers have praised the knowledgeable guides and the exciting yet safe nature of the trips offered by Paddle Moab.
name: Paddle Moab- Raft, Kayak, SUP, and Canyon Co.
address: 44 W 200 N, Moab, UT 84532, USA

detail_description: High Point Hummer and ATV Tours and Rentals in Moab offers exciting and family-friendly tours for all ages. Visitors have raved about the sunset ride at Hell's Revenge, where they drove their own vehicles or joined a tour group. The knowledgeable guides, such as JP and Jenna, ensure a safe and enjoyable experience while providing interesting insights about the trails. Guests appreciated the thoughtful touches like water and granola bars during the adventure.
name: High Point Hummer and ATV Tours and Rentals
address: 301 S Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Modern suites in a casual hotel featuring a gym & an outdoor pool, plus free breakfast & parking.
detail_description: Comfort Suites Moab near Arches National Park is a modern hotel with well-appointed suites, a fitness center, and an outdoor pool. Guests can enjoy complimentary breakfast and parking during their stay. The hotel's convenient location, just five miles from the entrance of Arches National Park and one mile from the city center, makes it an ideal choice for travelers looking to explore the area's natural attractions.
name: Comfort Suites Moab near Arches National Park
address: 400 N Main St, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Casual American dining in a lodge setting, with options including steaks, seafood, pasta & barbecue.

The menu features a variety of delectable dishes including steaks, seafood, pasta, and barbecue, with the sweet potato fries being a standout favorite. The restaurant's Far West atmosphere is reflected in its two-story wooden structure, complete with a fireplace indoors and a saloon-style porch outdoors.
name: The Broken Oar Restaurant
address: 53 W 400 N, Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Upscale hotel offering a sleek steakhouse/bar & an outdoor pool, plus a fitness center & a spa.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Moab, Hoodoo Moab, Curio Collection by Hilton is an upscale retreat that perfectly blends luxury with adventure. Just a short drive from the breathtaking Arches National Park, this stylish hotel offers a plethora of amenities designed for relaxation and recreation. Guests can indulge in a full-service spa experience or unwind at the seasonal outdoor pool after exploring the stunning desert landscapes.
name: Hoodoo Moab, Curio Collection by Hilton
address: 111 N 100 W, Moab, UT 84532, USA

detail_description: Moab Valley, located in Utah, is a haven for adventure enthusiasts. Surrounded by two national parks, the Colorado River, and vast expanses of public land, it offers endless opportunities for hiking, climbing, mountain biking, and paddling. The area's unique rock formations attract climbers from around the world. Visitors can also enjoy exclusive views of the valley and nearby attractions like Arches National Park. Additionally, Moab offers diverse cultural experiences and post-adventure dining options to satisfy any appetite.
name: Moab Valley
address: Moab, UT 84532, USA

excerpt: Colorful cafe offering burgers, chops & other standards, plus a tapas menu in a relaxed atmosphere.
detail_description: Twisted Sista's Cafe is a vibrant and relaxed eatery that offers a diverse menu featuring burgers, chops, tapas, soups, salads, sandwiches, and meat entrees. The cafe also caters to special dietary needs with options for gluten-free, vegetarian, and vegan diners. While the majority of the dishes are meat-based, they do offer one vegan option - an Indian curry. Customers have praised the friendly service and quick food preparation despite busy periods.
name: Twisted Sista's Cafe

detail_description: Momentum Mountain Biking offers an exhilarating way to explore Dead Horse Point State Park with unique views that can't be experienced from the scenic drive or overlooks. The mountain biking tours are led by knowledgeable and passionate guides who ensure a safe and enjoyable experience while pushing the limits and improving skills. The meticulous event planning by the organizers makes the trip stress-free, providing transportation, delicious meals, and attention to every detail.
